  card_002,general,medium,"What is a key clinical utility of digital variance angiography (DVA) in interventional radiology procedures?","DVA allows for a significant reduction in radiation dose during stationary image acquisitions, enhancing patient safety during procedures like prostatic artery embolization.",Digest;DVA;Radiation Dose;Interventional Radiology
  card_003,pulmonary,hard,"In patients with pulmonary metastases from soft tissue or bone sarcoma, what baseline CT imaging parameters have been shown to predict overall and progression-free survival?","This study identified parameters such as tumor size, number of lesions, and involvement of specific lung regions as prognostic factors on baseline CT imaging.",Digest;Pulmonary Metastases;Sarcoma;Prognosis;CT
  card_004,cardiology,medium,"What is the primary goal of quantifying net water uptake on non-contrast CT in the acute setting of ischemic stroke?","Quantifying net water uptake helps to differentiate between different types of acute ischemic stroke and can provide prognostic information regarding infarct core size and potential for reperfusion.",Digest;Stroke;Water Uptake;CT;Diagnosis
  card_005,news,easy,"What recent business development highlights a trend in the radiology industry?","Envision Radiology recently acquired Rezolut, a private equity-backed imaging center operator, indicating continued consolidation within the radiology market.",Digest;Industry News;Mergers & Acquisitions;Consolidation

